# documents / typst

Typst is a modern markup-based typesetting system (Apache-2.0, Rust) — a TeX
alternative for academic, legal, and long-form documents. Write `.typ` markup,
compile to a PDF (or SVG/PNG) with a single self-contained binary; no TeX install,
incremental compilation, scriptable markup.

controls do
  documents.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  documents.format: { label: "Output format", type: "select", options: "pdf, png, svg" }
  documents.ppi: { label: "Raster resolution (ppi, png only)", type: "range", min: 72, max: 600, step: 24 }
  documents.body: { label: "Document source (.typ)", type: "textarea", file: "src/main.typ" }
end

## Required reading
- claude-skill-typst (community, lucifer1004) — https://github.com/lucifer1004/claude-skill-typst
- Typst official docs llms.txt (Typst GmbH) — https://typst.app/docs/llms.txt
- Typst Documentation / Reference (Typst GmbH, Apache-2.0) — https://typst.app/docs/
- Typst in Production (community guide) — https://typst-in-production.com/

## Render
```bash
# install (macOS)
brew install typst

# compile to PDF (default)
typst compile src/main.typ out/main.pdf

# or raster / vector export
typst compile --format png --ppi 144 src/main.typ out/main.png
typst compile --format svg src/main.typ out/main.svg

# parametrized templates: pass values into the document
typst compile --input title="My Doc" src/main.typ out/main.pdf

# live preview while editing
typst watch src/main.typ out/main.pdf
```

## Failure modes
- `typst: command not found` — run `brew install typst` (self-contained, no TeX).
- Imports/assets not found — set `--root` to the project root so relative paths resolve.
- Custom fonts not picked up — pass `--font-path <dir>`.
- `--ppi` only affects raster (png); ignored for pdf/svg output.
- Markup gotchas: headings use `=`, bold is `*text*`, code/scripting uses `#`.
- Non-reproducible PDFs across builds — pin the timestamp for byte-stable output.
